Everything in this repository is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

This means that you are free to use serverbot as long as you don't use any part of it for any commercial purpose and context or as part of any system that is being used for any commercial purpose or context. People and non-profit organizations without commercial activities are free to use it as they please. You are also allowed to share and adapt serverbot, as long as you:

- Give appropiate credits (name of creator/parties, license and disclaimer notice, link to serverbot etc.).
- Publicly indicate all (previous) changes and modifications to all parts of serverbot.
- Distribute serverbot's code under the exact same license (no other licenses allowed without permission).

More information on the license can be found at:
http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

Despite this being one of the more restrictive licenses around, we're actually quite flexible. Sent an email to mail@nozel.org if you think you should be able to use this for free or when you are in doubt whether you are allowed to use this software. You can also sent an email when you want to buy the software for usage within a commercial context.
